views.text: 2 cups dark chocolate, broken into small pieces

views.text: 1. In a large bowl combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
2. In a separate bowl, mix the butter, caster sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until smooth.
3. Add the eggs and the flour to the mixture and beat to combine.
4. Add the chocolate pieces and stir.
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]com.tudorspan.recipekeeper:id/txtItem[text]4. Add the chocolate pieces and stir.[enabled,,]

views.text: 5. Drop well rounded spoonfuls of dough onto a greased cookie sheet.
7. Remove from the oven and place cookies on a wire rack to cool.
